{"version": 2, "width": 80, "height": 30, "timestamp": 1784143944, "env": {"TERM": "xterm-256color"}}
[0.0085, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[2J\u001b[3J\u001b[1mDARc — Deep Adversarial Review CLI\u001b[0m\r\nIterative adversarial review: Claude self-review + OpenAI GPT-5.6 cross-model\r\n\r\n"]
[1.011688, "o", "\u001b[0;36mTarget: gilded_rose.py (47 lines, 6 levels of nesting)\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[1.013198, "o", "# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\r\n\r\nclass GildedRose(object):\r\n\r\n    def __init__(self, items):\r\n        self.items = items\r\n\r\n    def update_quality(self):\r\n        for item in self.items:\r\n            if item.name != \"Aged Brie\" and item.name != \"Backstage passes to a TAFKAL80ETC concert\":\r\n                if item.quality > 0:\r\n"]
[1.013245, "o", "                    if item.name != \"Sulfuras, Hand of Ragnaros\":\r\n                        item.quality = item.quality - 1\r\n            else:\r\n                if item.quality < 50:\r\n"]
[1.014092, "o", "    ...\r\n"]
[1.014634, "o", "\r\n"]
[2.016166, "o", "\u001b[1m$ /darc:1 gilded_rose.py\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.018069, "o", "\r\n\u001b[0;36m═══ Round 1 (Self) — Claude adversarial review ═══\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[4.019748, "o", "\r\n"]
[4.019995, "o", "\u001b[0;31mCRITICAL\u001b[0m — Missing Conjured item handling\r\n  Evidence: No conditional for 'Conjured' in update_quality() (lines 8-36)\r\n  Fix: Add conjured path — degrade by 2 (or 4 after sell-by)\r\n\r\n"]
[5.521778, "o", "\u001b[0;31mHIGH\u001b[0m — Magic string anti-pattern\r\n  Evidence: 'Aged Brie' repeated at lines 10, 27. 'Backstage passes' at 10, 17, 28.\r\n  Fix: Extract item name constants\r\n\r\n"]
[6.523759, "o", "\u001b[0;31mHIGH\u001b[0m — Obscured quality reset\r\n  Evidence: Line 33 — item.quality = item.quality - item.quality\r\n  Fix: Replace with item.quality = 0\r\n\r\n"]
[7.525775, "o", "\u001b[1;33mMEDIUM\u001b[0m — Nesting depth of 6\r\n\u001b[1;33mMEDIUM\u001b[0m — Duplicate bounds checks (quality < 50 in 4 places)\r\n\u001b[0mLOW\u001b[0m — No docstring or type hints\r\n\r\n"]
[8.527837, "o", "\u001b[0;36m6 findings total: 1 CRITICAL, 2 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM, 1 LOW\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[10.029573, "o", "\u001b[0;36m═══ Round 1 (OpenAI GPT-5.6) — Cross-model verification ═══\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[11.031588, "o", "\r\n\u001b[0;31mHIGH\u001b[0m — Conjured items not implemented\r\n"]
[11.031688, "o", "\u001b[0;31mHIGH\u001b[0m — Quality invariants not enforced for arbitrary input\r\n\u001b[1;33mMEDIUM\u001b[0m — Behavior selected via fragile exact-name strings\r\n\u001b[1;33mMEDIUM\u001b[0m — Update logic deeply duplicated, hard to verify\r\n\u001b[1;33mMEDIUM\u001b[0m — Mutable public fields allow invariants to change at any time\r\n"]
[11.031724, "o", "\u001b[1;33mMEDIUM\u001b[0m — No validation of item objects or field types\r\n\u001b[0mLOW\u001b[0m — Magic values and duplicated literals obscure rules\r\n\u001b[0mLOW\u001b[0m — Backstage expiration reset unnecessarily obscure\r\n"]
[11.03262, "o", "\u001b[0mLOW\u001b[0m — No tests cover boundary behavior\r\n\r\n"]
[12.533896, "o", "\u001b[0;36m9 findings total: 2 HIGH, 4 MEDIUM, 3 LOW\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[12.53419, "o", "\r\n"]
[13.538665, "o", "\u001b[1m═══ Round 1 Synthesis ═══\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[13.538882, "o", "\r\nCross-model agreement: Conjured missing, magic strings, deep nesting.\r\nCross-model complement: Self-review caught x-x code smell;\r\n  OpenAI caught constructor validation + mutable-field risks.\r\nNeither model found everything alone.\r\n\r\n"]
[15.540742, "o", "\u001b[0;32m15 findings across two model families.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[16.542686, "o", "\u001b[1mApplying fixes — strategy pattern refactoring\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[17.544666, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[0;32m✓\u001b[0m Extracted named constants\r\n  \u001b[0;32m✓\u001b[0m Quality helpers (directional clamping)\r\n"]
[17.545604, "o", "  \u001b[0;32m✓\u001b[0m Predicate functions for item classification\r\n  \u001b[0;32m✓\u001b[0m Strategy dispatch — one function per item type\r\n  \u001b[0;32m✓\u001b[0m Conjured items handled (case-insensitive)\r\n\r\n"]
[18.546675, "o", "47 lines → 118 lines. 6 levels of nesting → 1.\r\n\r\n"]
[19.549921, "o", "# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-\r\n\"\"\"\r\nGilded Rose inventory system.\r\n\r\nBusiness rules (GildedRoseRequirements.md):\r\n- All items have SellIn (days to sell) and Quality (how valuable).\r\n- Each day SellIn decreases by 1 (except Sulfuras).\r\n- Normal items: Quality -1/day; -2 after sell-by. Minimum 0.\r\n- Aged Brie: Quality +1/day; +2 after sell-by. Maximum 50.\r\n- Sulfuras: Legendary. Quality always 80, never changes, no sell-by.\r\n- Backstage passes: +1 normally; +2 when <=10 days; +3 when <=5 days;\r\n  drops to 0 after concert (sell-by < 0). Maximum 50.\r\n- Conjured items: degrade twice as fast (-2/day; -4 after sell-by).\r\n  Detected by name containing \"Conjured\" (case-insensitive). Minimum 0.\r\n\r\n"]
[19.549994, "o", "IMPORTANT: The Item class definition must not be modified (goblin rule).\r\nAll item classification is done via name string matching.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nfrom typing import List\r\n"]
[19.550842, "o", "    ...\r\n"]
[19.551141, "o", "\r\n"]
[21.052997, "o", "\u001b[1m$ /darc:1 gilded_rose.py\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[22.055937, "o", "\r\n\u001b[0;36m═══ Round 2 (OpenAI GPT-5.6) ═══\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[23.057916, "o", "\r\nCode-level: sell-in boundaries, quality caps, Sulfuras exemption,\r\n  strategy precedence, Conjured detection — all correct.\r\n\r\n"]
[24.059757, "o", "\u001b[1;33m\u001b[1mMEDIUM\u001b[0m\u001b[1;33m — Sulfuras quality invariant is self-contradictory\u001b[0m\r\n  The spec says quality is both \"always 80\" AND \"never changes.\"\r\n  For non-80 input, these rules conflict. Code alone cannot resolve this.\r\n\r\n"]
[26.061391, "o", "\u001b[1;33m\u001b[1mMEDIUM\u001b[0m\u001b[1;33m — Quality bounds rely on caller discipline\u001b[0m\r\n  The constructor accepts any value. Spec says quality is never negative\r\n  and never exceeds 50, but does not say whose job enforcement is.\r\n\r\n"]
[28.063162, "o", "\u001b[0;36m0 CRITICAL, 0 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[29.065127, "o", "\u001b[1m═══ Structural Escalation ═══\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nAfter 3+ rounds, DAR detects these are structural:\r\n  they cannot be fixed in code alone.\r\n"]
[29.065401, "o", "\r\n"]
[31.06729, "o", "\u001b[1mProposed resolutions:\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n1. Sulfuras: require quality==80 at construction (reject otherwise).\r\n   'Always 80' takes precedence over 'never changes.'\r\n"]
[31.067371, "o", "\r\n2. Input validation: reject non-Sulfuras quality outside 0-50.\r\n   Fail fast — silent clamping hides caller errors.\r\n\r\n"]
[34.069531, "o", "\u001b[1mAlternative perspectives:\u001b[0m\r\n\r\nPerhaps 'never changes' was written for the common case\r\n  and 'always 80' is the authoritative rule.\r\n\r\n"]
[34.069597, "o", "Consider whether the contradiction exists because Sulfuras\r\n  was added after the other rules and never reconciled.\r\n"]
[34.069988, "o", "\r\nOne perspective: if Sulfuras enters with quality 79, perhaps\r\n  the real-world answer is 'that cannot happen' rather than\r\n  'the code should handle it.'\r\n\r\n"]
[38.072145, "o", "\u001b[1m═══ Final Synthesis ═══\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[38.0728, "o", "\r\nCode-level: 15 findings → resolved.\r\nStructural: 2 findings → documented, resolutions proposed.\r\nHuman decision required for the Sulfuras quality contract."]
[38.073137, "o", "\r\n\r\n"]
[40.074825, "o", "\u001b[0;32mDAR does not rubber-stamp.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[41.076711, "o", "\u001b[0;36mDARc — Deep Adversarial Reviews\u001b[0m\r\ngithub.com/oxygn-cloud-ai/deep-adversarial-reviews\r\n\r\n"]
